name: BulkUpdateTeamMembers
description:
Update multiple team members in bulk.

This tool updates multiple team member objects at once. It should be called when you need to perform bulk updates to team members. While processing, if any updates fail, the tool still returns the updated members along with specific error details for the failed attempts.

parameters.name: team_members_update_data
parameters.description: JSON object containing updates for `TeamMember` objects. Each key is a `team_member_id` mapping to `UpdateTeamMemberRequest`. Maximum of 25 updates.

team_members.description:
The data used to update the `TeamMember` objects. Each key is the `team_member_id` that maps to the `UpdateTeamMemberRequest`.
The maximum number of update objects is 25.

For each team member, include the fields to add, change, or clear. Fields can be cleared using a null value.
To update `wage_setting.job_assignments`, you must provide the complete list of job assignments. If needed,
call [ListJobs](api-endpoint:Team-ListJobs) to get the required `job_id` values.

value_schema.description:
An object containing the fields to POST for the request.

See the corresponding object definition for field details.
